node.text:
It’s time to feed the gators 🐊 and they sure do love their chicken 🍗 I like to cut it up because although they could eat the whole thing 🐓 it is good enrichment to be able to grab so many pieces 🤷‍♂️ and it’s easier on their tummies 😃 just like when mom always told you to make sure you chew your food 😂 have fun with us in this feeding frenzy IGTV 📺 
.
.
.

node.text:
Never judge a book by its cover 📕 especially when it comes to snake eggs... we like to give every single one a chance... and this is exactly why! No matter what it’s about: snake eggs 🥚 the start of your day 📅 or the people you meet 🚶even the worst starts can turn out good 👍 
.
.
.

node.title: Don’t Judge a Book by its Cover 📖

.

.
.
.

node.text:
Spotted this pile of junk on the side of the road and each time I visited we found some epic rattlesnakes 🐍 this junk serves as an artifical reef for all sorts of animals 🐁🦎🕷 of course never handle rattlesnakes or any venomous snakes like I do 🚫 it is a good idea to never bother any wild snake as you may never know if it is venomous or not 🤷‍♂️ better safe than sorry!
.
.
.

Asian water monitors are hunters but mainly scavangers 🍴 eating just about anything they come across in the wild🍗 that's why they can eat so much at once so quick 😳 because they never know when their next meal is going to be 🤷‍♂️ But that doesn't mean they can't have their first pics 🤔 so lets see what Fabio decides to eat first this time around 🤩 its usually never the same order 😂 
.
.
.

node.text:
This maybe even cooler than helping my baby snakes hatch 😳 I got to help two baby sharks 🦈 hatch out of their eggs at the @sanantonioaquarium  their eggs are actually called mermaid purses 🧜‍♀️ and the babies sometim'es need help because like my snakes they don't always ahve the easiest time getting out 🤷‍♂️ wow are they amazing 🙌
.
.
.

node.text:
It’s time to feed the gators 🐊 and they sure do love their chicken 🍗 I like to cut it up because although they could eat the whole thing 🐓 it is good enrichment to be able to grab so many pieces 🤷‍♂️ and it’s easier on their tummies 😃 just like when mom always told you to make sure you chew your food 😂 have fun with us in this feeding frenzy IGTV 📺 
.
.
.
#reptile #animal #alligator #crocodilian #chef #cheflife #chicken #lunch #feedingfrenzy #notapet #invasivespecies #igtv #igtvchannel #video #style

node.text:
Happy World Snake Day 🐍 I’ve been in love with snakes since I was a kid 👦 with nothing to do except catch snakes in ditches and fields 🤷‍♂️ and over 50 years later I’m still the kid who loves snakes that never grew up 😂 snakes are amazing animals and truly misunderstood and I am glad I have been able to change so many peoples views on such incredible animals 🙌🙌 and if you don’t totally like snakes yet I get it 🙏 but hopefully that changes soon if you’ve been following me for a while 🤔 or this might be the wrong account for you 😂 Happy World Snake Day 🌎🐍 
.
.
.
#worldsnakeday #reptile #snake #snakes #python #retic #rattlesnake #viper #boa #animals #nature #beautiful #amazing #wildlife #learn #conservation #insta #photo #style

node.text:
What will this gigantic tiger eat 😳 I decided to bring a variety to share with one of @docantle’s kids and wow is it amazing to watch the relationship they have 🐅 Tigers are incredible animals both very intelligent and extreme powerful 💪 definitely something I wouldn’t want to do without one of the pros like Doc around 🙌 enjoy this epic IGTV and see if this big boy eats in the order you guess 🤔 
.
.
.
